# Task Scoping Protocol

## Pre-flight checklist before touching app.py
Answer all three before the agent writes a single line of code:

1. **Which route or function?** (e.g. `/api/nodered/deploy`, `deploy_nodered()`)
2. **What exactly needs to change?** (1–2 sentences — bug description or desired behavior)
3. **Approximate line range?** (run a Grep to anchor before reading)

If you cannot answer all three → run a Grep/SemanticSearch first. Do NOT start with open-ended exploration in Agent mode.

## If the task touches >3 functions, split it
Large scope = large context = expensive and error-prone. Break into sub-tasks, write a brief plan, execute each in its own chat.

## Prefer Grep over open-ended file reads
- ❌ SemanticSearch "find where Node-RED context backup happens" (reads many chunks)
- ✅ `Grep "nodered_context_backup" app.py` (immediate, zero context cost)

## State the release version at the start of every chat
infra-TAK is at **v0.8.9-alpha**. Always open by saying which version you're working against so the agent doesn't re-read the README to orient itself.

## When reporting a bug, include the symptom + the log line
- ❌ "The deploy is broken"
- ✅ "Deploy fails at the context backup step — log shows `FileNotFoundError` on `/opt/tak/nodered-ctx-backup.json`"

The difference is ~2,000 tokens of back-and-forth investigation vs. going straight to the fix.
